  <section class="typography-section">
    <header class="typography-section__header">
      <div class="typography-section__badge">Standards</div>
      <h2 class="typography-section__title">Responsive Typography & Accessibility</h2>
      <p class="typography-section__description">
        Key principles for responsive text scaling and WCAG 2.2 compliance.
        These ensure readability on all devices and for all users without exceptions.
      </p>
      <div class="typography-section__meta">
        <span class="meta-item"><strong>Standard:</strong> WCAG 2.2 Level AA</span>
        <span class="meta-item"><strong>Testing:</strong> Zoom 200%, screen readers, keyboard navigation</span>
        <span class="meta-item"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Contrast 4.5:1 (body), 3:1 (large)</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="typography-demo__content">
      <h3>Design Principles</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Always use appropriate heading levels and inline elements</li>
        <li><strong>Font Scaling:</strong> Use rem-based sizes (1rem = 16px) for user-controlled sizing</li>
        <li><strong>Line Height:</strong> Maintain 1.5+ for body text (--leading-normal: 1.5)</li>
        <li><strong>Contrast:</strong> WCAG AA minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (18pt+)</li>
        <li><strong>Font Weight:</strong> Avoid using color alone for emphasis; use weight variation</li>
        <li><strong>Spacing:</strong> Use letter-spacing (--tracking-*) sparingly for headlines only</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Accessibility Checklist</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>✅ Headings form a logical outline (no skipped levels like h1 → h3)</li>
        <li>✅ Focus indicators visible on all interactive text (links, buttons)</li>
        <li>✅ Text is not justified (hyphens can interfere with screen readers)</li>
        <li>✅ Color is never the only indicator of meaning (use weight, icons, text)</li>
        <li>✅ Links are underlined or otherwise distinguished from body text</li>
        <li>✅ Lists use semantic markup (&lt;ul&gt;, &lt;ol&gt;, &lt;dl&gt;)</li>
        <li>✅ Form labels are properly associated with inputs</li>
        <li>✅ Code blocks are escaped and syntax-highlighted appropriately</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Responsive Scaling</h3>
      <p>
        The typography scale is designed to adapt to viewport size via media queries.
        Font sizes scale smoothly from mobile to desktop, maintaining readability
        without explicit breakpoint declarations in component CSS.
      </p>
      <p>
        Developers should test text on multiple devices and support browser zoom
        (100–200%) to verify accessibility and responsiveness.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


